stimulusHtml: ​A data set of coordinate pairs is modeled by the function fθ=sinθ{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"}. If the model f{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"} is consistent with the data set, which of the following should describe the dependent variable values on the interval π<θ<3π2{"digitSeparatorsAsMN":"auto"} ?
choicesHtml: ​The values should be decreasing at a decreasing rate on the interval.
​​The values should be decreasing at an increasing rate on the interval.
​The values should be increasing at a decreasing rate on the interval.​
​​The values should be increasing at an increasing rate on the interval.
